{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_219","type":"agent_message","text":"The geometry check confirmed a real desktop overflow: within the stage pane, the audio stage gets about `456px` of width, and the inherited two-column sticky-summary layout is too wide for that container. I’m switching the audio stage to a single-column stack so the summary cards stop colliding with the segment list inside the existing workspace shell."}}
